track_title = "Sergeant Kilro's Theme"
track_lyrics = "[INTRO - INSTRUMENTAL (fast build)]
(Orchestra hits → guitars enter → double-kick ramps. Heroic motif.)

[VERSE 1 (driving, lower phrasing)]
When the roof turns coal and the night runs hot,
I hear the call—then I move, I don’t stop.
No throne to chase, no gold to hold—
Only the oath, and the iron cold.

[PRE-CHORUS (rising, chant-like)]
Step by step—hold the ground.
Shields up high—feel the sound.
If fear comes close, let it show—
I don’t break. I don’t go.

[CHORUS (HUGE, baritone chant)]
SERGEANT KILRO—IRON WALL!
I take the fire before you fall!
Hear the drum in my heartbeat pound,
I’m the vow that holds this ground!
SERGEANT KILRO—HOLD THE LINE!
Till the black turns out to light!
Through the storm, through the smoke, through the blows—
You live… if I say so!

[VERSE 2 (more intense)]
They come like wolves on a blood-wet road,
But I’m the shield—so the weak can hold.
Steel on steel, and the world turns loud,
I stand in front—like stone, like proud.

[PRE-CHORUS 2 (higher, still low-register)]
Lock it in—don’t let it bend,
Shoulder to shoulder—end to end.
If fate wants in, let it try—
It pays in full… tonight.

[CHORUS (repeat, choir punches)]
SERGEANT KILRO—IRON WALL!
I take the fire before you fall!
Hear the drum in my heartbeat pound,
I’m the vow that holds this ground!
SERGEANT KILRO—HOLD THE LINE!
Till the black turns out to light!
Through the storm, through the smoke, through the blows—
You live… if I say so!

[BRIDGE (half-time → explosive lift)]
(Brief drop: orchestra + choir, then guitars.)
I was forged where hope ran thin,
I learned what grit is born within:
Not “no fear” in my blood—
But “not one more” in the mud.

[SOLO (shred lead over orchestra)]
(Guitar solo, then drum fill back into final chorus.)

[FINAL CHORUS (VERY HUGE)]
SERGEANT KILRO—IRON WALL!
I take the fire before you fall!
Raise the horns, let the war-drums roll,
I guard the flame, I guard the soul!
SERGEANT KILRO—HOLD THE LINE!
Till the dawn cuts clean and bright!
Through the storm, through the smoke, through the blows—
You live… if I say so!

[OUTRO - INSTRUMENTAL (victory sprint)]
(Orchestra + guitars hit the motif, hard final chord.)"
